gomodel:SYNGO_886  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper uses immunogold electron microscopy to define the localization of Calcium /Calmodulin kinase II alpha in pre- and postsynaptic terminals at rest and following neuronal activity induced by high K+.\nFigure 2 presents a quantification of the distribution of a-CaMKII immunolabel in three regions of the synapse. A significant fraction of particles can be found in the 200 nm region proximal to the presynatpic membrane and at the dendritic spine.\nFigures 3a,b show immunogold labeling for a-CaMKII at the periphery of the synaptic vesicle clusters and at the postsynaptic compartment.\nFigures 4c, d show that immunogold labeling of a-CaMKII is localized at the edge of clustered synaptic vesicles in control terminals (C), but after high K+, label\nbecomes intermingled with declustered vesicle (D).\nFigures 5a,b show that a-CaMKII immunogold labeling becomes redistributed closer to the active zone after high K+ depolarization.. Experimental description: Hippocampal cell cultures were prepared and maintained as described in Lu et al. (1998). Briefly, hippocampal cells from 21-day old embryonic Sprague-Dawley\nrats were dissociated and grown on top of a feeder layer of glial cells for 3-4 weeks." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_886" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

